# Changelog

All notable changes to the Mudae Harem Sorter will be documented in this file.

## [1.5.0] - 2026-04-08

v1.5.0 — 2026-04-08
🚀 Added
New Stats modal with:
Total Characters
Locked Characters
Total Kakera
Total Spheres
Unique Series
Characters with Notes
Most Valuable Characters (Top 5)
Perk Distribution (Perk 10 unlocked, Full maxed)
Series Breakdown (count + total kakera)
New generic confirm dialog system for destructive actions.
New toast notification system for unified user feedback.
New modal stack handling with:
Escape-to-close top modal
Overlay click-to-close
Body scroll lock while modals are open.
ID-based character model with UUID fallback for stable operations.
Delegated grid action handling via data-action buttons.
Image update modal flow for per-character image URL edits.
Series move confirmation modal before moving series under locked section.
Help modal updates documenting current workflows and stats.
✨ Improved
Refactored render flow into renderAndSave() for consistent UI + persistence updates.
Improved merge flow:
Updates kakera, spheres, perks, series, and notes for existing characters.
Prompts before applying detected image URL changes.
Improved copy workflows:
Ctrl/Cmd+Click card to copy character name.
Per-box copy button feedback for generated command boxes.
Improved command generation:
Auto-splits long $sm output into safe chunks.
Uses $smpos chaining across boxes.
Improved note tools:
Quick Notes setup (8 slots)
Per-character quick/custom note apply
Exact-match $n note export with auto chunking.
Improved sorting behavior and tie-break consistency (notably SP sort fallback logic).
Improved search matching across character name, series, note, perks, and SP.
🧹 Changed
Stats modal cleanup:
Removed Average Kakera
Removed Average Spheres
Removed Least Valuable Characters section
Updated stats computation logic to match cleaned modal content.
Updated Help content to reflect current feature set.
Version bumped to v1.5.0 in:
Top bar label
Help modal title
Local save metadata
Downloaded JSON save metadata
🛠️ Technical / Internal
Consolidated reusable helpers (escapeHtml, character ID helpers, modal helpers).
Added safer load/import handling with validation and graceful failure messaging.
Standardized UI state persistence through local storage save points.

v1.4.2 — 2026-04-07
🚀 Added
Full Spheres (SP) and Perks support from:
$mmai-k-z+z!s
$mmai-kz+z!s
Character cards now display:
Total SP invested
Perk status
Added 💠 Sort by Spheres with tie-breaking:
Primary: SP (High → Low)
Tie 1: Kakera (High → Low)
Tie 2: Name (A → Z)
✨ Improved
Parser overhauled for more reliable handling of:
Series headers
Notes
SP values
Complex perk strings
Better edge-case handling for long/complex series names.
SP styling now matches kakera accent color for consistency.
Help modal instructions improved for export-copy workflow.
🧹 Changed
"Full" perks now shown as All Perks Maxed.
Characters with no investment now show:
0 sp
No perks
instead of ambiguous placeholders.
🛠️ Technical
Version bumped to 1.4.2.
Save file metadata version updated to 1.4.2 (backward compatible).
Search expanded to include SP values and perk text.

v1.3.0 — 2026-04-06
🚀 Added
Full Notes system:
Persistent per-character notes
Green note pill on each card
Quick Notes Setup:
8 reusable note slots from top 📝 Note menu
Note editor modal:
Quick note buttons
Custom note input
Note management actions:
Clear note (single character)
Clear all notes
Note Export:
Generates ready-to-paste $n name$name$name$note commands
Auto-splits output to stay within Discord character limits
✨ Improved
Help modal fully reorganized and expanded for clarity/readability.
Added clear guidance for importing new characters into existing sorted lists.
Added thank-you message in Help modal.
🐛 Fixed
🗑️ Clear now fully resets:
Harem
Locks
Output
Quick note slots
Sort by Note now correctly preserves locked-section behavior.
🧹 Changed
Version display updated to v1.3.0.
🛠️ Technical
Notes now persist with saved harem data.
Minor robustness updates in note apply/clear flows.

v1.2.0 — 2026-04-06
🚀 Added
New import option when list already exists:
Replace entire list
Add new characters to bottom
Add-to-bottom behavior:
Deduplicates by character name
Appends only new characters
Preserves existing order/locks
Import textarea now auto-clears after successful import.
Added toast notifications for import feedback.
Added Help section for importing into existing lists.
Ctrl + Click on card copies character name to clipboard.
🐛 Fixed
Help button functionality corrected.
Clear button now fully clears list and UI.
Jump to Bottom now scrolls to true grid bottom.
🧹 Changed
Version bumped to 1.2.0.
Help modal updated with new import workflow guidance.

v1.1test — 2026-04 (pre-1.2.0)
🚀 Added
Full save/load system:
Auto localStorage
Manual JSON download/upload
Paste JSON import
Slim top bar with uniform buttons.
Fixed sidebars positioned at 775px from center.
Ctrl + Click name copy.
Position counters on each card (x/y).
Note display as green pills.
Search support for character and series.
Navigation sidebar:
Top
End of Locked
Bottom
Return to Last Position
Jump to Output
Improved $sm generation:
Proper $smpos chaining
Per-box copy buttons
🐛 Fixed
Series detection improvements (including DanMachi and long titles).
Multiple layout/button alignment issues from earlier builds.

v1.0 — Initial Stable Release
🚀 Added
Core Mudae export parser ($mmak-i-s / $mmaki-s support).
Drag-and-drop grid with locked section pinning.
Per-card controls:
Move up/down
Move series
Lock/Unlock
Sorting by:
Name
Series
Kakera
(reverse on second click)
Shuffle unlocked characters.
$sm command generation with automatic splitting.
Help modal with usage instructions.
Initial save system foundation.

